The paper discusses decision-making processes and their optimization, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of bounded rationality is also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of non-equilibrium thermodynamics to quantify inefficiencies suggests a connection to materials science (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO).
